This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance and space requirements of learned indexes for database management systems (DBMS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for building and updating indexes, which suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with data structures and algorithms for indexing, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of indexes for search and prediction also suggests a connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
